  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>Reporting directly to the Group Finance Manager, you will be responsible to:</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Handle the full set of accounts from source documents to financial statements, including accounts payable, accounts receivable, general ledger, and fixed assets. </li><li>Perform monthly and year-end closing, including preparation of management accounts, schedules, and variance analysis.</li><li>Prepare timely and accurate financial and management reports for group consolidation and management review.</li><li>Prepare and submit statutory filings, including GST returns and corporate income tax.</li><li>Liaise independently with external auditors, tax agents, vendors, and regulatory authorities.</li><li>Prepare audit schedules and support external audit processes, including audited financial statements.</li><li>Perform balance sheet reconciliations, intercompany reconciliations, and detailed account analysis.</li><li>Maintain proper accounting records and documentation in compliance with Singapore Financial Reporting Standards (SFRS/FRS).</li><li>Monitor cash flow, manage payments, collections matters to ensure smooth day-to-day operations.</li><li>Support management with ad-hoc financial analysis, budgeting, forecasting, and other finance-related duties as required. </li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in Accountancy, Finance, or a related discipline.</li><li>Professional qualification such as Chartered Accountant (CA), ACCA, or CPA is an added advantage.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant working experience in Finance/Accounting.</li><li>Strong hands-on experience in maintaining a full set of accounts independently.</li><li>Good working knowledge of Singapore Financial Reporting Standards (SFRS/FRS), GST, and corporate taxation.</li><li>Highly independent, self-motivated, and able to work with minimal supervision.</li><li>Able to manage multiple priorities, meet tight deadlines, and work under pressure.</li><li>Meticulous, responsible, and confident with strong problem-solving skills.</li></ul>",
